LIMIT :
It is used to return the specified number of records.
The LIMIT clause is useful on large tables with thousands of records. 
Returning a large number of records can impact performance.

SYNTAX : SELECT * FROM < table name >
         WHERE <condition> 
         LIMIT <value> ;

# selects the first three records from the "users" table, whose grnder is "M" -
SELECT * FROM users 
WHERE gender="M"
limit 3;

# selects the first two records from the "users" table, where the state is "maharashtra":
SELECT * FROM users 
WHERE state="maharashtra"
limit 2;

# selects the first four records from the "users" table, where the gender is "F"
SELECT id , name, contact FROM users 
WHERE gender="F"
limit 4;
